TAMPA — Round Two of the “Battle of Florida” is set to begin Tuesday at FLA Live Arena in Sunrise. After Calgary defeated Dallas in overtime to finish out the first round late Sunday, the league released the Round 2 schedules. Florida-Tampa Bay will begin Tuesday at 7 p.m. and could run as late as May 29 if the best-of-seven series goes the distance. The teams will have two days off between Games 2 and 3 — there is a Kane Brown concert at Amalie Arena on Saturday — and play will resume Sunday afternoon at 1:30 p.m. in Tampa. Games will air on TNT for those in either market. Round 2 schedule Game 1 – Lightning at Panthers, 7 p.m. Tuesday Game 2 - Lightning at Panthers, 7 p.m. Thursday Game 3 – Panthers at Lightning, 1:30 p.m. Sunday Game 4 – Panthers at Lightning, 7 p.m. Monday, May 23 Game 5 – Lightning at Panthers, TBD Wednesday, May 25  *if necessary Game 6 – Panthers at Lightning, TBD Friday, May 27 *if necessary Game 7 – Lightning at Panthers, TBD Sunday, May 29 *if necessary Contact Mari Faiello at mfaiello@tampabay.com. Follow @faiello_mari. • • • Sign up for Lightning Strikes, a weekly newsletter from Bolts beat writer Eduardo A. Encina that brings you closer to the ice. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.